The project focuses on analytics for a large scooter rental service. The company provided three datasets containing user data, their annual rides, and subscription pricing. The goal was to analyze user demographics and scooter usage patterns, as well as determine the potential benefits of introducing paid scooter subscriptions.


Data Description:
1) Users Table (users_go.csv)
* user_id — Unique user identifier.
* name — User name.
* age — Age.
* city — City.
* subscription_type — Subscription type: free, ultra.

2) Rides Table (rides_go.csv)
* user_id — Unique user identifier.
* distance — Distance in meters traveled by the user in the current session.
* duration — Session duration in minutes, i.e., the time from the moment the user clicked the "Start Ride" button until they clicked the "End Ride" button.
* date — Date of the trip.

3) Subscriptions Table (subscriptions_go.csv)
* subscription_type — Subscription type.
* minute_price — Price per minute of a ride for this subscription.
* start_ride_price — Start price of a ride.
* subscription_fee — Monthly payment fee.


pandas version: 1.2.4
matplotlib version: 3.3.4
scipy.stats 1.13.1
